{"id":14881753,"mediaExerciseId":"b67e07ff-5aa9-49b1-ab41-5bf8fe2e3f81","exerciseName":"2","chapterName":"21","chapterTitle":"International Corporate Finance","groupId":612464,"groupTitle":"Concept Questions","isPremium":true,"sectionName":"21.2","sectionTitle":"Foreign Exchange Markets and Exchange Rates","pageNumber":718,"solutions":[{"id":5961107,"modifiedOn":"2021-01-01T00:00:00.000000","steps":[{"columns":[{"text":"In this exercise, we are asked to define a triangle arbitrage, 90-day forward exchange rate, and an exchange rate of SF 1.90.","images":{"latex":{"large":{"height":66,"srcUrl":"https://d2nchlq0f2u6vy.cloudfront.net/21/12/29/386fc17b0cdbc4816f40fc499f2bab96/3f2bcd904d7cfb4fbe629f4d187047f3/lateximg_large.png","width":996},"regular":{"height":34,"srcUrl":"https://d2nchlq0f2u6vy.cloudfront.net/21/12/29/386fc17b0cdbc4816f40fc499f2bab96/3f2bcd904d7cfb4fbe629f4d187047f3/lateximg.png","width":498}},"additional":null},"hasInvalidKatex":false,"isTextOnly":true}],"isResult":false,"stepNumber":1},{"columns":[{"text":"## 2a.\n\nWe are asked to define a triangle arbitrage.","images":{"latex":null,"additional":null},"hasInvalidKatex":false,"isTextOnly":false}],"isResult":false,"stepNumber":2},{"columns":[{"text":"**Cross-rate** is an exchange rate between two currencies that is computed by a third currency. Doing cross-rate exchange will give rise to a **triangle arbitrage** which is an activity that moves *three different exchange rates*.","images":{"latex":{"large":{"height":105,"srcUrl":"https://d2nchlq0f2u6vy.cloudfront.net/21/12/29/386fc17b0cdbc4816f40fc499f2bab96/f06562745ec2f5bee7c6197fd2584851/lateximg_large.png","width":995},"regular":{"height":53,"srcUrl":"https://d2nchlq0f2u6vy.cloudfront.net/21/12/29/386fc17b0cdbc4816f40fc499f2bab96/f06562745ec2f5bee7c6197fd2584851/lateximg.png","width":499}},"additional":null},"hasInvalidKatex":false,"isTextOnly":false}],"isResult":false,"stepNumber":3},{"columns":[{"text":"## 2b.\n\nWe are asked to define a 90-day forward exchange rate.","images":{"latex":null,"additional":null},"hasInvalidKatex":false,"isTextOnly":false}],"isResult":false,"stepNumber":4},{"columns":[{"text":"An **Exchange Rate** is the value of a country's currency when expressed in another country's currency. A **forward trade** is an agreement to exchange currency in the future.\n\\\nThe **forward exchange rate** is the exchange rate that is agreed by the parties when the forward trade was made. It will be used in the future.","images":{"latex":{"large":{"height":176,"srcUrl":"https://d2nchlq0f2u6vy.cloudfront.net/21/12/29/386fc17b0cdbc4816f40fc499f2bab96/be9395c95ff7315eb2aae136b0d6096f/lateximg_large.png","width":997},"regular":{"height":89,"srcUrl":"https://d2nchlq0f2u6vy.cloudfront.net/21/12/29/386fc17b0cdbc4816f40fc499f2bab96/be9395c95ff7315eb2aae136b0d6096f/lateximg.png","width":498}},"additional":null},"hasInvalidKatex":false,"isTextOnly":false}],"isResult":false,"stepNumber":5},{"columns":[{"text":"Therefore, a **90-day forward exchange rate** is the exchange rate that is agreed by the parties when the forward trade was made and will be used *after 90 days* or when the exchange happens 90 days after the forward trade was made.","images":{"latex":{"large":{"height":138,"srcUrl":"https://d2nchlq0f2u6vy.cloudfront.net/21/12/29/386fc17b0cdbc4816f40fc499f2bab96/e8c8cf8a12a04f281f70e52f22fcebe7/lateximg_large.png","width":996},"regular":{"height":70,"srcUrl":"https://d2nchlq0f2u6vy.cloudfront.net/21/12/29/386fc17b0cdbc4816f40fc499f2bab96/e8c8cf8a12a04f281f70e52f22fcebe7/lateximg.png","width":498}},"additional":null},"hasInvalidKatex":false,"isTextOnly":false}],"isResult":false,"stepNumber":6},{"columns":[{"text":"## 2c.\n\nWe are asked to define an exchange rate of SF 1.90.","images":{"latex":null,"additional":null},"hasInvalidKatex":false,"isTextOnly":false}],"isResult":false,"stepNumber":7},{"columns":[{"text":"An Exchange Rate is the value of a country's currency when expressed in another country's currency.  Therefore, an exchange rate of SF 1.90 indicates that **for every $1, you will get 1.90 Swiss francs.**","images":{"latex":null,"additional":null},"hasInvalidKatex":false,"isTextOnly":false}],"isResult":false,"stepNumber":8},{"columns":[{"text":"As a conclusion, we have defined a triangle arbitrage, 90-day forward exchange rate, and an exchange rate of SF 1.90.","images":{"latex":{"large":{"height":66,"srcUrl":"https://d2nchlq0f2u6vy.cloudfront.net/21/12/29/386fc17b0cdbc4816f40fc499f2bab96/ae1ebdc8f11e557e41b32e1da43dc7ae/lateximg_large.png","width":1011},"regular":{"height":34,"srcUrl":"https://d2nchlq0f2u6vy.cloudfront.net/21/12/29/386fc17b0cdbc4816f40fc499f2bab96/ae1ebdc8f11e557e41b32e1da43dc7ae/lateximg.png","width":506}},"additional":null},"hasInvalidKatex":false,"isTextOnly":true}],"isResult":false,"stepNumber":9}],"rating":5,"solutionUuid":"a03aaa57-d4e8-4aed-8d21-5aa24af9c1c1","editorVersion":2,"answeredOn":null,"ratingCount":null,"solutionOrder":null,"totalSteps":9}],"textbook":{"authors":"Bradford D. Jordan, Randolph W. Westerfield, Stephen A. Ross","imageUrl":"https://d2nchlq0f2u6vy.cloudfront.net/textbook_covers/tmpm0p82b7h","imageThumbnailUrl":"https://d2nchlq0f2u6vy.cloudfront.net/cache/d1/d3/d1d34d106dd29dd2e71be582412ef59d.jpg","id":34320,"isbn":"9781259918957","isPremium":true,"title":"Fundamentals of Corporate Finance","edition":"12th Edition","verifiedSolutionCount":1217,"shouldBeIndexableForSeo":true,"modified":1665448474394,"active":true,"publisher":"McGraw-Hill Education","mainTextbookIsbn":null,"subjects":{"level1":["Social Science"],"level2":["Economics"],"level3":["Finance"]}},"nextExercises":[{"id":14881754,"exerciseName":"3","page":721,"hasSolution":true,"mediaExerciseId":"179f9827-e779-4dbd-b9fd-a902d56a42f6","_webUrl":"https://quizlet.com/explanations/textbook-solutions/fundamentals-of-corporate-finance-12th-edition-9781259918957/chapter-21-concept-questions-3-179f9827-e779-4dbd-b9fd-a902d56a42f6"}],"previousExercises":[{"id":1488